# Plan: Custom Theme System

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal light/dark/system toggle stored in `t3code:theme` (values: `"light" | "dark" | "system"`). The goal is to add a full custom theme system: typed `Theme` definitions in `packages/shared`, a richer `useTheme()` hook with CSS-variable injection in the web app, and a visual theme selector in the Settings page.

The existing `DiffWorkerPoolProvider` (`apps/web/src/components/DiffWorkerPoolProvider.tsx`) consumes `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"` from `useTheme()`—this must be preserved to avoid breaking diff rendering.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` | **Create** — theme types + 3 built-in themes + `getTheme` / `listThemes` |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | **Modify** — add `./themes` subpath export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` | **Replace** — new hook returning `{ theme, setTheme, availableThemes, resolvedTheme }` |
| `apps/web/src/index.css` | **Modify** — add CSS vars for font-family and font-size-base; add sidebar/editor/terminal/status-bar vars |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **Create** — theme picker component with color swatches |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | **Modify** — swap out the Appearance radio-group for `<ThemeSelector />` |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### 1 · `packages/shared/src/themes.ts`

Follow the style of `model.ts` — pure exported functions, no framework imports.

```ts
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly dark: boolean;        // used by DiffWorkerPoolProvider
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
  readonly fontFamily: string;
  readonly fontSize: number;     // px
}
```

Define `BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly Theme[]` with three entries:

- **`t3-dark`** (default, `dark: true`): near-neutral-950 background, neutral-100 foreground, oklch purple accent — matches current dark-mode palette.
- **`t3-light`** (`dark: false`): white background, neutral-800 foreground, oklch purple accent — matches current light-mode palette.
- **`t3-midnight`** (`dark: true`): deep navy background, blue-tinted foreground, cyan-blue accent.

Export:
```ts
export function listThemes(): readonly Theme[]
export function getTheme(id: string): Theme | undefined
```

`DEFAULT_THEME_ID = "t3-dark"` exported constant.

### 2 · `packages/shared/package.json`

Add to `"exports"`:
```json
"./themes": {
  "types": "./src/themes.ts",
  "import": "./src/themes.ts"
}
```

### 3 · `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (full replacement)

Follow the **exact same `useSyncExternalStore` module-level pattern** as the existing file. Key changes:

- **Storage key**: new key `t3code:theme-id` (avoids collision with old `t3code:theme`).
- **Migration**: if `t3code:theme-id` is absent but `t3code:theme` is `"light"` → default to `"t3-light"`; `"dark"` → `"t3-dark"`; `"system"` or missing → `"t3-dark"`.
- **`applyTheme(theme: Theme, suppressTransitions?)`**:
  - Toggle `.dark` class based on `theme.dark`.
  - Set inline CSS custom properties on `document.documentElement`:
    - `--background`, `--foreground` from theme colors.
    - `--primary`, `--ring` from `theme.colors.accent`.
    - `--sidebar-background`, `--editor-background`, `--terminal-background`, `--status-bar-background` from remaining color fields.
    - `--theme-font-family` from `theme.fontFamily`.
    - `--theme-font-size-base` as `${theme.fontSize}px`.
  - Keep transition-suppression logic (`.no-transitions` class).
- **Apply on module load** (before React renders, same as existing file):
  ```ts
  applyTheme(resolveStoredTheme());
  ```
- **Hook return**:
  ```ts
  export function useTheme() {
    // ...useSyncExternalStore...
    return {
      theme,                            // Theme object
      setTheme,                         // (id: string) => void
      availableThemes: listThemes(),    // readonly Theme[]
      resolvedTheme,                    // "light" | "dark" — derived from theme.dark
    } as const;
  }
  ```

`resolvedTheme` is `theme.dark ? "dark" : "light"` — this is what `DiffWorkerPoolProvider` consumes; no changes needed there.

### 4 · `apps/web/src/index.css`

Add to `:root {}` block (after existing variables):
```css
/* Theme system — overridden by useTheme via inline style */
--theme-font-family: "DM Sans", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif;
--theme-font-size-base: 14px;
--sidebar-background: var(--background);
--editor-background: var(--background);
--terminal-background: var(--background);
--status-bar-background: var(--background);
```

Update `body` rule to consume the font variables:
```css
body {
  font-family: var(--theme-font-family);
  font-size: var(--theme-font-size-base);
  /* ... existing margin/padding/min-height unchanged */
}
```

> The inline styles set by `applyTheme` on `:root` override these defaults with higher specificity, so themes work without touching the stylesheet on each change.

### 5 · `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

Create a new component. Follow the **existing radio-button pattern** from `_chat.settings.tsx` (the current `THEME_OPTIONS` section) but extend it with color swatches.

```tsx
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme, availableThemes } = useTheme();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme">
      {availableThemes.map((t) => {
        const selected = theme.id === t.id;
        return (
          <button key={t.id} type="button" role="radio" aria-checked={selected}
            className={`flex w-full items-center justify-between rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 text-left transition-colors ${
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground"
                : "border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent"
            }`}
            onClick={() => setTheme(t.id)}
          >
            {/* Swatches */}
            <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div className="flex gap-1">
                {[t.colors.background, t.colors.foreground, t.colors.accent].map((color, i) => (
                  <span key={i} className="inline-block h-4 w-4 rounded-full border border-black/10"
                    style={{ background: color }} aria-hidden="true" />
                ))}
              </div>
              <span className="flex flex-col">
                <span className="text-sm font-medium">{t.name}</span>
              </span>
            </div>
            {selected && (
              <span className="rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                Selected
              </span>
            )}
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 6 · `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

- Remove `THEME_OPTIONS` constant and the `resolvedTheme` usage.
- Remove the existing radio-group `<div>` (lines ~210–243) that renders light/dark/system buttons.
- Import `ThemeSelector`.
- Replace the removed JSX with `<ThemeSelector />`.
- Update the "Active theme:" line below it to use `theme.name`:
  ```tsx
  const { theme, setTheme } = useTheme(); // resolvedTheme no longer needed here
  // ...
  <p className="mt-4 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    Active theme: <span className="font-medium text-foreground">{theme.name}</span>
  </p>
  ```

---

## CSS Variable Mapping (Theme → DOM)

| Theme field | CSS custom property set on `:root` |
|---|---|
| `colors.background` | `--background` |
| `colors.foreground` | `--foreground` |
| `colors.accent` | `--primary`, `--ring` |
| `colors.sidebar` | `--sidebar-background` |
| `colors.editor` | `--editor-background` |
| `colors.terminal` | `--terminal-background` |
| `colors.statusBar` | `--status-bar-background` |
| `fontFamily` | `--theme-font-family` |
| `fontSize` | `--theme-font-size-base` |

---

## No-Change Components

- `apps/web/src/components/DiffWorkerPoolProvider.tsx` — consumes `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"` which is preserved.
- All other components — consume existing CSS variables (`--background`, `--foreground`, etc.) which are now controlled by inline styles from `applyTheme`.
- Build config, `vite.config.ts`, `turbo.json` — no changes.
- No new npm dependencies.

---

## Verification

1. Run `bun typecheck` from repo root — must pass with no new errors.
2. Run `bun lint` from repo root — must pass.
3. Open the web app → Settings → Appearance section shows three theme buttons with color swatches.
4. Select "T3 Midnight" → app background changes to deep navy, accent changes to cyan-blue; localStorage key `t3code:theme-id` = `"t3-midnight"`.
5. Reload the page → midnight theme persists (no flash before theme applies).
6. Open a diff panel — diff rendering uses the correct light/dark diff theme.
7. Verify `getTheme("t3-dark")` and `listThemes()` are importable from `@t3tools/shared/themes` in the browser build.

